# S04-T01: Score Panel

## Objective
`ScorePanel` — top-of-screen glass card showing score, streak, and level badge.
Uses `glass-panel` utility from `index.css`. `memo`-wrapped per code style standard.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Score increments animate via GSAP count-up (not instant jump).
- Streak row hidden when streak = 0.
- Level badge visible, color `bg-secondary text-white`.
- Component is `memo`-wrapped.

## Steps
1. Create `src/components/ScorePanel.tsx`.
2. Props: `score: number`, `streak: number`, `level: number`. Wrap in `memo`.
3. Layout: `flex justify-between items-center px-4 py-2 glass-panel`.
4. Score: `<span>` with `text-score text-secondary font-bold`. On `score` change:
   `gsap.fromTo(scoreRef, {scale:1.3}, {scale:1, duration:0.25, ease:'back.out(2)'})`.
5. Streak row: `{streak > 0 && <span className="text-primary font-bold">🎵 ×{streak}</span>}`.
6. Level badge: `<span className="bg-secondary text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">L{level}</span>`.
7. `git commit -m "feat: ScorePanel component"`.
